.docname {Custom figure}
.include {_Setup.qd}

The **`.figure {caption?} {body}`** adds generalization to the [image figures](Figure.qd) syntax extension, as it allows for any content to be handled as a *figure* block, which:
- May feature a caption;
- Can be numbered (see [*Numbering*](Numbering.qd)).

```markdown
## Custom figures

.figure {My caption.}
    .container padding:{1cm} background:{yellow}
        Hello, world!
```

